    url: "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EnyAF7yRQ7c",
    docUrl: "https://www.westonwi.gov/AgendaCenter/ViewFile/Agenda/_04212026-1908",
    isAgendaOnly: false,
    badge: "new",
    overview: "The Village of Weston Tourism Commission approved four grant requests totaling $22,500 for upcoming events including the Mountain Bay Cup soccer tournament, GG's 5K Glow Fun Run, Hmong Wausau Festival, and Wisconsin Valley Fair. The commission also scheduled a special meeting for May 18th to consider a late application from the Taste and Glow Balloon Festival.",
    agenda: [
      { time:"0:07", item:"Call to order and Pledge of Allegiance" },
      { time:"0:45", item:"Roll call" },
      { time:"1:00", item:"Public comments" },
      { time:"4:15", item:"Approval of minutes from previous meeting" },
      { time:"4:30", item:"Acknowledge 2025 budget status report" },
      { time:"5:00", item:"CVB reports presentation by Tim White" },
      { time:"14:15", item:"Grant request - Mountain Bay Cup soccer tournament" },
      { time:"22:15", item:"Grant request - GG's 5K Glow Fun Run Walk" },
      { time:"27:30", item:"Grant request - Hmong Wausau Festival" },
      { time:"32:30", item:"Grant request - Wisconsin Valley Fair" },
      { time:"38:00", item:"Post-event report - High School Bowling" },
      { time:"40:00", item:"Discussion of Taste and Glow Balloon Festival application and special meeting scheduling" },
    ],
    discussions: [
      { item:"CVB Reports", body:"Tim White, Visit Wausau Executive Director, provided updates on upcoming events including the Wisconsin Bike Fed summit and the World Horseshoe Tournament. White noted registrations for the horseshoe tournament are ahead of last year's Salt Lake City event (644 participants) with expectations of 800+ participants this year. He introduced new Director of Operations Jamie Rice Hecondorf and acknowledged missing the Taste and Glow Balloon Festival grant application, taking personal responsibility for the oversight. White addressed public comment concerns about hotel capacity, stating there are approximately 2,400 rooms in the greater Wausau area and about 1,800 in the immediate metro area." },
      { item:"Grant request - Mountain Bay Cup", body:"Dan Kubat, tournament director for MC United Soccer Club, presented a request for $5,000 for the May 1-3 spring soccer tournament. He reported 170 teams registered with 68.5% (approximately 116 teams) traveling from more than 90 miles away, expecting 8,000-10,000 attendees and an economic impact of $700,000 to $1 million. This is the first time requesting funds for the spring tournament (fall tournament previously funded at $3,500). Motion by Renee, seconded, approved unanimously." },
      { item:"Grant request - GG's 5K Glow Fun Run Walk", body:"Erica presented online for GG's Playhouse, requesting $2,500 for their sixth annual 5K glow fun run at Weston YMCA. She noted they've secured WAOW for advertising and are adding a cornhole tournament this year. The event attracts out-of-state participants from Minnesota, Texas, Michigan, and Illinois. Motion by Renee, seconded by Jackson, approved unanimously." },
      { item:"Grant request - Hmong Wausau Festival", body:"Elang Jang, festival chair since 2017, requested $10,000 for the August 1-2 event. Last year drew 12,000-13,000 attendees, making it the largest Hmong festival in Wisconsin. This year they're adding under-18 volleyball and soccer tournaments expecting an additional 500-800 athletes plus family members, projecting 14,000-15,000 total attendees. Jang noted hotels within an hour fill up for the event. Motion by Hushin, seconded by Renee, approved unanimously for $10,000." },
      { item:"Grant request - Wisconsin Valley Fair", body:"No representative was present to speak. Commission members noted the application requested $10,000 but last year they approved only $5,000. Concerns were raised about limited direct benefit to Weston, with the application showing only 3-4 hotel rooms booked and hotels listed being in Wausau and Rothschild rather than Weston. Commission discussed that most attendees are local and don't stay overnight. Motion by Hushin for $5,000, seconded by Renee, approved unanimously." },
      { item:"Taste and Glow Balloon Festival scheduling", body:"Staff noted Tim White missed submitting the Taste and Glow application, which needs consideration before the July event. The commission scheduled a special meeting for May 18th at 4:00 PM to handle this single agenda item, ahead of the regular July 20th meeting." },
    ],
    publicComment: "Jim Pensson of 5500 Street, Weston, spoke via online connection questioning how applicants report 2,000 hotel room bookings when he believed this exceeds Weston and greater Wausau capacity. He also asked for clarification on how many rooms are actually in Village of Weston versus other areas, and questioned follow-through on previous commitments to coordinate with Weston businesses.",
